1771 February 13 John Norton to Robert
                                C. Nicholas, discusses Nicholas's continued business ventures;
                                Refers to some British financial issue concerning Colonel Tucker and
                                Mr. Hunter; Norton is having a new ship Virginia built at Ipswich;
                                Explains that the possibility of war with Spain is diminishing yet
                                he still hesitates to plan trips,

1771 May 04 James Buchanan to Robert C.
                                Nicholas, apologizes for his misplaced faith in Messrs. Dunmoor and
                                for the delay in the transfer of the goods,

1794 April 08 Receipt, for Land Office
                                Warrants from Wilson Cary Nicholas in name of William Patterson;
                                signed by [Hudson?] Martin

1841 August 31 Henry Page to Thomas
                                Jefferson Randolph. Informs Randolph that his daughter Martha will
                                return to the [Edgehill School] in the Fall,
